Definition: a pernicious and malign influence that is hard to get rid of
Example: racism is a pestilence at the heart of the nation; according to him, I was the canker in their midst
Synonyms: adj, all, noxious, pestilent, canker, influence, a, pernicious, and, malign, that, is, hard, to, get, rid, of, racism, at, the, heart, nation, according, him, I, was, in, their, midst
Category: noun.cognition
